Mob Psycho 100 revolves around Kageyama Shigeo, known also as  "Mob" (hence the title), a socially awkward eighth-grader with powerful psychic abilities. Despite his extraordinary powers, Mob desires a normal life and suppresses his emotions to avoid unleashing his psychic energy uncontrollably. He works part-time for a self-proclaimed psychic named Reigen Arataka, who exploits Mob's abilities for financial gain. The series explores themes of self-discovery, personal growth, and the consequences of unchecked power, blending intense action sequences with humour and psychological depth.

